Articles.Content:
I\'m new to modeling parts in KSP. I was wondering if anyone could help me solve this error. After I finish modeling the part, making the config, textures.. ect. I run into this error when trying to load the part for the first time.

'A load handler for this file type does not yet exist'

I am exporting it in the Collada/dea Format.

I\'ve double checked the collision mesh (node_collider)

Strangely, I don\'t run into this problem when I\'m using a simple cube.

I\'ve done some searching on the forums, but with no success. I\'m sure it\'s just a simple error on my part. Any help would be much appreciated. -Kidd
Know that error, and I\'m a plugin dev, not part creator. I\'m sure it could be caused by a wrong config file, maybe post .dae and .cfg here so I could check them

Thanks for the quick reply.

I\'ve attached both, The part it\'s self is only a cylinder.

Thanks!

This has been bothering me for hours, all over a simple typo...

Anyways, thanks again!
